PUBLIC Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane released 117 reports in a virtual media briefing on Wednesday, 30 June. The reports included housing, healthcare, Home Affairs, cadre deployment and ministers’ adviser appointment. One was related to investments made with VBS Mutual Bank. Her office investigated allegations of irregular appointment of ministerial advisers. The accusers had alleged Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula and his director-general irregularly appointed advisers, contrary to provisions of the Public Service Act. She said the accusers alleged that Mbalula, and Alec Moemi, irregularly appointed Advisors in the Ministry of Transport. She said the investigation revealed that the appointments were contrary to the provisions of the Public Service Act and other prescripts applicable to the department. “It also revealed that three of the appointees were irregularly paid salaries.”